nes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n25696","n25697","n25698","n25699"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strike, to beat, to hit","examples":[{"text":"ضَرَبَ رَأْسَهُ بِٱلْجِدَارِ","english":"He hit his head against the wall."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shoot at, to fire at, to bombard","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to play"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to type (on a keyboard or typewriter)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to impose, to inflict","examples":[{"text":"ضُرِبَتْ عَلَيْهِمُ الذِّلَّةُ أَيْنَ مَا ثُقِفُوا إِلَّا بِحَبْلٍ مِنَ اللَّهِ وَحَبْلٍ مِنَ النَّاسِ","english":"Ignominy shall be their portion wheresoever they are found save (where they grasp) a rope from Allah and a rope from men."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to leave, to abandon, to turn away from, to forsake"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sting (of a scorpion)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pitch (a tent)","examples":[{"text":"ضَرَبَ خَيْمَةً","english":"to pitch a tent"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to coin, to mint, to strike"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to seal, to stamp"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to erase"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cast, to throw, to set, to put","examples":[{"text":"ضَرَبَ الفَخًّا عَلَى الطَائِرِ","english":"he threw the snare over the bird"},{"text":"ضَرَبَ بَيْنَهُمَا سَدًْا","english":"he set a barrier between (the two of) them"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be long (of the night)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to set or posit as an example or make a simile of, to be proverbial with","examples":[{"text":"خِلَاط\nبكَسر أوله، وآخره طاء مهملة: بلدة عامرة مشهورة كثيرة الخيرات، وهى قصبة أرمينية الوسطى، يضرب ببردها فى الشتاء المثل، وبُحَيْرَتُها يُجلَبُ منها السمك الطّرّيخ، [على وزن سكّين] ^(«٣») ، ليس فى غيرها، يُحمَلُ إلى سائرِ البلاد البعيدة، وهى من العجب، فإنها عشرة أشهر لا يوجد فيها حيوان، لا سمك ولا غيره، ثم يَظهر بها السمك مدة شهرين، فيُصاد ويكبس.","english":"Xlat: A flourishing, famous town, full of amenities, it is a fortress of Central Armenia, and its burd clothing sets an example in winter, and there is Lake Van whence one imports the pearl mullet, to which there is no equal, which is carried to the rest of the towns far away, it’s wonderful, ten months the animal is not found therein, no fish nor anything, then there appears fish for two months, and is caught and pickled."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to multiply","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pulsate, to throb, to beat (of a vein or the heart)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ache violently, to hurt severely (of a wound or tooth)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to roam, to travel","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to migrate (of a bird)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cruise (of a ship)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to incline, to tend, to shade","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"قرنوة: الغافقي: قال قوم أنها الهرنوة والقرنوة أيضاً حشيشة. […] قال أبو حنيفة: هي عشبة يضرب ورقها إلى الحمرة وهي مرة يدبغ بها. وقال أيضاً عن بعضهم: هي خضراء غبراء على ساق لها ثمرة كالسنبلة ومنابتها السهول وهي مرعى. وقال آخر: القرنوة عشبة يطول ورقها كورق الحندقوقا عفصة تستعمل في دباغة الجلود وقيل أنها هذه الحشيشة المعروفة بالأنجبار.","english":"Aloeswood. Al-Ġāfaqīy: Some say that these seeds of aloe are a herb. […] Abū Ḥanīfa: The tender leaves of this herb tend towards red and this is when they are used for tanning. And some authors said they are dingy towards the foot and have fruits like ears like spikes growing on plains and used for pasturage. Another said: It’s a plant of long leaves like honey lotus the gall of which is used for tanning hides and it has been said it is a herb known as al-anjabār."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mount (a female camel)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mix","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to get the better of in beating"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be smitten by hoarfrost or rime"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to give a violent hit, give a sound blow"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to beat violently or repeatedly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mix, mix up"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stir up discord"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sew on a lining or padding"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to drink of the milk called ضَرِيب (ḍarīb, “milk of several camels in the same bucket”)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to get overtaken by the snow (ضَرِيب (ḍarīb, “snow, hoarfrost, ice”))"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be deep-set (of an eye)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَرَبَ (ḍaraba, “to beat”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beating, striking, hitting"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"violence, power"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"haste, hurry"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the playing of musical instruments"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"minting"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"multiplication"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"make, form, fashion, mold, cast"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sort, species"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"report of a gun"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"similarity"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"last foot of the second hemistich"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"who beats much"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"brave, bold"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active, clever"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"of a slender make and not fleshy"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"slight, light"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"beaten"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"coined"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"similar, like"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضُرِبَ (ḍuriba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَرِبَ (ḍariba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/dˤa.ra.ba/","/dˤa.ri.ba/","/dˤu.ri.ba/","/dˤa.ru.ba/","/dˤar.ra.ba/","/dˤarb/","/dˤa.rab/"]}